Funhouse is the fifth studio album by pop singer Pink,
set to be released across Europe on October 24, 2008. The
album&#039;s lead single, "So What", has been the biggest solo
success of Pink&#039;s career to date, topping the charts in
eleven countries so far, including her native United
States, and also in the UK, and reaching the top 10 in
many others.

Originally, Pink wanted to call her album &#039;Heartbreak is
a Motherfucker&#039; but her record label declined this
decision because of the fear of lack of sales due to
offensive language. (LOL)
